<br>
So, a lot of people have suggested splitting the extra 10 levels -- 5 to Novice CH to give that step an actual reward and 5 to MCH to help distinguish the true master.<br>
<br>
Also, the whole point of the profession vs. class system is to encourage some level of dabbling.  In other words, I'm not sure people who get a bit of CH are really a problem -- isn't that what the system is supposed to allow you to do?<br>
<br>
